## 2. State Machine Map

The booking state machine is the highest-risk component. All valid transitions must be preserved exactly:

```
pending ──(accept)──► accepted ──(start)──► in_progress ──(complete)──► completed ──(payment)──► paid
   │                     │
   └──(cancel)──► cancelled ◄──(cancel)──┘
   │
   └──(auto-timeout at T+60s)──► cancelled
```

### State Transition Guards (must not change)

| Transition | From | To | Guard |
|---|---|---|---|
| accept | `pending` | `accepted` | Worker must not be blocked |
| start | `accepted` | `in_progress` | No additional guard |
| complete | `in_progress` | `completed` | No additional guard |
| cancel (no fee) | `pending` | `cancelled` | Clears active timer |
| cancel (fee) | `accepted` | `cancelled` | Records `metadata.cancellationFee = {amount: 50}` |
| auto-timeout | `pending` | `cancelled` | Triggered by 60s in-memory timer |
| payment verify | `completed` | `paid` + `paymentStatus: paid` | `status === 'completed'` strict check |

### Side Effects Per Transition (must not change)

| Transition | Socket Event | Telegram | Timer |
|---|---|---|---|
| create | `booking:new` → worker socketId | `sendBookingAlertToWorker` | Start 60s countdown |
| accept | `booking:accepted` → customer socketId | — | Cancel countdown |
| start | `booking:started` → `booking_{id}` room | — | — |
| complete | `booking:completed` → `booking_{id}` room | — | — |
| cancel | `booking:cancelled` → `booking_{id}` room | — | Cancel countdown if pending |
| auto-timeout | `booking:timeout` → `booking_{id}` room | — | Self-clears |

